comments.body:
AFAICT, this bug was already present in 0.15.1, and perhaps before.
The problem is basically this snippet in {{IpcFormatWriter::RecordBatch}}:
{code:c++}
    if (!wrote_dictionaries_) {
      RETURN_NOT_OK(WriteDictionaries(batch));
      wrote_dictionaries_ = true;
    }
{code}

The solution isn't entirely trivial: presumably we don't want to write dictionaries again when they are identical. We also don't want to compare them every time. Perhaps compare them by pointer?
